1) SqlTransaction-----  System.Data.SqlClient;

 u need work with opening & closing
1 database--1 server


------------------------------------
2)TransactionScope---- System.Transactions
m server--m databases---- open or close the connections for the respective database though on differnet servers



============================================================
SqlConnection sqlConnection db = new SqlConnection("ConnectionString");    
SqlTransaction transaction;    
  
sqlConnection.Open();    
transaction = sqlConnection.BeginTransaction();    
try     
{    
   new SqlCommand("INSERT Qwery1", sqlConnection, transaction)    
      .ExecuteNonQuery();    
   new SqlCommand("INSERT Qwery2 ", sqlConnection, transaction)    
      .ExecuteNonQuery();    
   new SqlCommand("INSERT Qwery3 ", sqlConnection, transaction)    
      .ExecuteNonQuery();    
   transaction.Commit();    
}     
catch (SqlException sqlError)     
{    
   transaction.Rollback();    
}    
sqlConnection.Close(); 
---------------------------

You can easily maintain one transaction for multiple databases or a single database with multiple connectionstrings, using TransactionScope.

When you use TransactionScope there is no need to close any Database connections in the middle.

using (TransactionScope transactionScope = new TransactionScope())
{

      try

      {

           method1() // Oracle DML operation

           method2() // Sql DML operation

           method3() // Oracle DML operation

           // transactionScope.complete()

           // transactionScope.Dispose();

      }

      catch (TransactionException ex)

      {

          transactionScope.Dispose();

          MessageBox.Show("Transaction Exception Occured");

      }

}
